LLM_response_editer_en:
On the current screen, in order to read the content on the screen, you usually do not need to perform any special operations, just read the text displayed on the screen with your eyes. But if you want to simulate scrolling on the screen to read more, you can use the mouse wheel or keyboard. According to the screen image provided, you may need to scroll down to continue reading. The following is the JSON format instruction to perform this operation:```json
[
    {"action_type": "MouseAction", "mouse_action_type": "scroll_down", "scroll_repeat": 3}
]
```The "scroll_repeat" specified here: 3 means that the scroll wheel scrolls down three times, and you can adjust this value according to the amount of content you need to read. If you need to turn the page to read more content or return, you can use the page turning button on the right side of the screen and set the corresponding mouse action for this purpose.
